Set Up a Google Cloud Storage Target Connection

After you create your Data Cloud instance, you can set up a Google Cloud Storage (GCS) connection.

Prerequisites

Complete the tasks in Set Up Permissions for the Google Cloud Storage Connector
Review the Data Cloud IP Allowlist and make sure the GCS Connection has necessary access.
In Data Cloud, select Data Cloud Setup.
Under Configuration, select Other Connectors.
Click New, and click Target.
Select Google Cloud Storage, and click Next.
Enter a connection name, connection API name, authentication details: access key, secret key, and connection details: bucket name and parent directory.
Access key	The access key generated during creation of the key in Google Cloud Storage platform
Secret key	The secret key generated during creation of the key in Google Cloud Storage platform.
Bucket name	The name of the bucket where you set up permissions in Google Cloud Storage platform.
Parent directory	The folder in the bucket where you want to transfer the data. It doesn’t include the bucket name.
IMPORTANT It’s recommended to use a different parent directory for source and target connection.
To review your configuration, click Test Connection.
Click Save.
